@NODE "QuickIntro" "Contents Rundown..."

@{code}@{jcenter}@{fg shine}Quick Introduction@{fg text}
@{jleft}
@{fg fill}Short:    @{fg text}DOpus5 Icons/Patterns/ARexx/Utils/Hints
@{fg fill}Uploader: @{fg text}Leo Davidson <leo@hampschl.demon.co.uk>
@{fg fill}Author:   @{fg text}Trevor Morris <a3nb@unb.ca>
@{fg fill}Type:     @{fg text}pix/mwb

@{body}@{fg shine}MWB_DOpus@{fg text} is the @{i}essential @{ui}add-on for all users of @{b}Directory Opus 5@{ub} - even
if you're not interested in @{b}MagicWorkbench@{ub} icons, we're sure you'll find
something useful and interesting! @{i}In fact, even if you don't use DOpus5,
you might like some of this!! @{ui}
@{par}@{code}
@{fg shine}@{u}Here's a brief list of what's inside the current version:@{fg text}@{uu}

@{fg fill}·@{fg text}  New/updated DOpus5 ARexx scripts.
@{fg fill}·@{fg text}  'C' and Assembler Utilities:
@{fg fill}->@{fg text} Add new/missing functions to Directory Opus 5.
@{fg fill}->@{fg text} Icon and palette manipulation (including a program to remap 8-colour
   MWB icons to work on screens of greater depth).
@{fg fill}·@{fg text}  Many, many high-quality MWB lister-toolbar icons to greatly improve
   the look of your DOpus5 (also perfect for ToolManager docks, too).
@{fg fill}·@{fg text}  Replacement MWB icons for DOpus5 program, iconified listers, etc.
@{fg fill}·@{fg text}  Some nice background patterns made specially for Directory Opus.
@{fg fill}·@{fg text}  A 100k AmigaGuide:
@{fg fill}->@{fg text} Many invaluable hints and tips on perfecting your DOpus5 setup.
@{fg fill}->@{fg text} A full hypertext guide to the contents of the archive.
@{fg fill}->@{fg text} Information on ordering DOpus5, and how to contact GPSoftware.
@{fg fill}·@{fg text}  A template to aid in the creation of your own icons.
@{fg fill}·@{fg text}  A few cool fonts.
@{fg fill}·@{fg text}  A survey, the results of which will go back to GPSoftware.
@{fg fill}·@{fg text}  Three pictures showing off the beauty and power of DOpus in
   combination with the MWB_DOpus icons and utilities.
@{fg fill}·@{fg text}  ...and some more bits and pieces for you to find and enjoy. @{bg shine}:-)@{bg back}

@ENDNODE

-------------------------------------------------------------------------------

@NODE "DownLoad" "What is this stuff?"
@NEXT "Requirements"

@{code}@{jcenter}@{fg shine}What is this stuff?@{fg text}
@{jleft}
The original archive should contain the following files:

 @{fg fill}@{" ARexx (dir)         " LINK "ARexx"    }          @{" Images (dir)        " LINK "Images"   }
 @{" c (dir)             " LINK "c"        }          @{" Images2 (dir)       " LINK "Images2"  }
 @{" Color&Pointer (dir) " LINK "C&P"      }          @{" Images3 (dir)       " LINK "Images3"  }
 @{" Fonts (dir)         " LINK "Fonts"    }          @{" Patterns (dir)      " LINK "Patterns" }
 @{" Icons (dir)         " LINK "Icons"    }@{fg text}
  ARexx.info                       @{b}Button_Template@{ub}
  Button_Template.info             C.info
  Color&Pointer.info               @{b}DOpusScreen.pic@{ub}
  DOpusScreen.pic.info             @{b}DOpus5Survey@{ub}
  DOpus5Survey.info                Fonts.info
  Icons.info                       Images.info
  Images2.info                     Images3.info
  @{b}MWB_DOpus.guide@{ub}                  MWB_DOpus.guide.info
  @{b}NudelScreen.pic@{ub}                  NudelScreen.pic.info
  @{b}NudelScreen2.pic@{ub}                 NudelScreen2.pic.info
  Patterns.info                    @{b}SYSOPS.README@{ub}
  SYSOPS.README.info

@{body}The @{b}Button_Template@{ub} is just a picture of everything in the Images drawers as
well as some extra stuff (it's handy as a template for drawing your own,
but if you do, make sure you upload them for everyone else to enjoy!)
@{par}
@{par}@{b}DOpusScreen.pic@{ub} is a snapshot of @{"my" LINK "Author"} DOpus screen which may give you some
ideas!
@{par}
@{par}@{b}NudelScreen.pic@{ub} is a snapshot of @{"Leo Davidson's" LINK "Author"} DOpus screen (even more
ideas for you A500 owners ;)
@{par}@{b}NudelScreen2.pic@{ub} is a very @{i}untidy @{ui}picture showing Opus doing lots of things
at once, so you get an idea of its power.
@{par}
@{par}@{b}MWB_DOpus.guide@{ub} - you are reading it ;)
@{par}
@{par}@{b}SYSOPS.README@{ub} is just a notice to BBS sysops regarding the naming convension
of this archive to try to avoid the situation where people accidentally
download the same archive twice (or more) because it has a different name.
@{par}
@{par}It would also be much appreciated if you would take the time to fill out the
@{b}DOpus5Survey@{ub} (all instructions are provided within).

@ENDNODE


@NODE "ARexx" "ARexx (dir)"
@TOC "Download"

@{code}@{jcenter}@{fg shine}ARexx (dir)@{fg text}
@{jleft}
This dir contains the following ARexx scripts written by @{"Leo Davidson" LINK "Author"}:

 CDO.dopus5                       CDO.dopus5.info
