@NODE "C&P" "Color&Pointer"
@TOC "Download"

@{code}@{jcenter}@{fg shine}Color&Pointer@{fg text}
@{jleft}
This drawer contains the following:

 ClickForColors                   ClickForColors.info
 ClickForPointer                  ClickForPointer.info

@{body}These are just my palette and pointer configs. Clicking on them will change
your prefs to emulate mine - but only until you reboot. The palette is quite
useful, as most times I draw things to look good using my palette (of course)
and it may not necessarily look good with yours!?

@ENDNODE


@NODE "Fonts" "Fonts"
@TOC "DownLoad"

@{code}@{jcenter}@{fg shine}Fonts@{fg text}
@{jleft}
@{body}This directory just contains a couple of fonts which some of you might like
to use for DOpus? Check out the NOoDLE & P0T fonts by @{"Leo Davidson" LINK "Author"}.
@{par}@{code}
 @{fg fill}P0T-IBM (dir)
 P0T-NOoDLE (dir)
 P0T-Prop (dir)
 PolarSmall-Prop (dir)
 PolarSmall (dir)@{fg text}
 P0T-IBM.font                     P0T-NOoDLE.font
 P0T-Prop.font                    PolarSmall-Prop.font
 PolarSmall.font

@ENDNODE


@NODE "Icons" "Icons"
@TOC "Download"

@{code}@{jcenter}@{fg shine}Icons@{fg text}
@{jleft}
This archive contains the following icons:

 AppIcon.info                Buttons.info                 Plain.info
 Environment.info            Filetype.info                System.info
 Group.info                  Lister.info                  Work.info
 Settings.info               DirectoryOpus.info           DOpus_Startup.info

@{body}I realize that, with the exception of Plain, System, and Work, DirectoryOpus,
and Opus5_Startup, these may look identical to the ones supplied with DOpus,
but they have been fixed. The original icons @{i}swim@{ui} when you click on them -
there were gliches in them which I fixed (I don't know why - it just bugged me
I guess!?! ;).  Plain, System, and Work (.info) are just three drive icons
which I made. If you want to use them you must change their type from @{b}drawer@{ub} to
@{b}drive@{ub} (I made them drawer-types so that you could see them in the archive -
drive icons would not have been visible).
@{par}
@{par}DirectoryOpus.info and Opus5_Startup.info are alternative @{"Magic WorkBench" LINK "MWB"} style
icons for DOpus. I drew the icons for myself, but hopefully someone else will
like them as well.

@ENDNODE


