@NODE "EVLhaDir" "LhaDir.DOpus5 1.0"
@NEXT "EVLhaDir"
@PREV "EVLhaDir"

@{code}@{jcenter}@{fg shine}LhaDir.DOpus5 1.0@{fg text}
@{jleft}
@{body}LhaDir.DOpus5 is an ARexx script for @{"Directory Opus 5" LINK "GPSoft"} that allows you to show
the contents of Lha archives in an Opus lister window and operate on the files
and directories inside the archive as if it is a normal directory.
@{par}@{code}
With LhADir.dopus5 you can:

· Browse through the directory structure of an archive file.
· Double click on files in an archive to read/play/show/etc (any DOpus internal
  command).
· Delete files and directories with the Delete button.
· Extract/add files and directories with the Copy or Move buttons.
· Double clicking on files and directories works.
· Can be compiled with the Rexx Plus Compiler for optimum speed.
· Works with more than one copy of Directory Opus running.
· View an archive in an archive by extracting it from it's mother archive to
  the current destination directory.
· Deletes strange filenames like '#?' without a problem.
· Create new (empty) Lha archives with the MakeDir button.
· Copy/move between two archives (via T:)
· Datestamps, attributes and comments are listed and preserved correctly.
· Localized (Dutch catalog provided).

LhaDir.DOpus5 is Copyright © 1995 by EAV Productions International.
Placed in the public domain. No restrictions on distribution or usage.

Author:   @{fg fill}Edmund Vermeulen@{fg text}
          Primulastraat 2
          3202 RN  Spijkenisse
          The Netherlands
          Tel. 01880-13925

Fidonet:  @{fg fill}2:286/407.48@{fg text}
Internet: @{fg fill}edmundv@grafix.xs4all.nl@{fg text}

@{fg shine}@{b}NOTE@{ub}: LhaDir.DOpus5 is included with the DOpus511.lha patch on Aminet @{fg text}

@ENDNODE


